instruction: Come up with a realistic conflict between two characters.
output: John and Alex are two brothers who have been embroiled in a long-standing feud. Despite coming from the same family, they have fundamentally different viewpoints on investments and financial advice. John often tries to give Alex advice, while Alex insists that it is his life and he should make his own decisions. This has created a rift between the siblings, with neither side willing to budge on their beliefs.
